content:
Replace the `std::mem::forget` with a proper connection lifecycle. Instead of forgetting the connection to prevent double-return, clone the connection handle before the retry and explicitly drop the original. Here's the fix:

```rust
// Before (leaks connection)
let conn = pool.get().await?;
if query_fails {
    std::mem::forget(conn); // LEAK!
    retry();
}

// After (proper lifecycle)
let conn = pool.get().await?;
if query_fails {
    drop(conn); // Return to pool
    let new_conn = pool.get().await?;
    retry_with(new_conn);
}
```
